==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Thalamus
<hw>Thal"a*mus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>; <plu><it>pl.</it>
<plw>Thalami</plw> <pr>(#)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L. <ets>thalamus</ets>
chamber, Gr. <grk>qa`lamos</grk>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>A mass of nervous matter on either side of the third ventricle of
the brain; -- called also <altname>optic thalamus</altname>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Same as
<er>Thallus</er>.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>The receptacle of a flower; a
torus.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Thalassian</ent>⟦br⟧
